# migrated from tests/cases/deepreason.chat (hermetic + isolated, perf-held)
[mock hermetic]
!set PARROT0_BASE=
!set PARROT0_SESSION=
!set PARROT0_WORLD_FACTS=0
!set PARROT0_LANG=en
!reset

[test deepreason]
!timeout 0
# deep-reasoning M3 (docs/plans/deep-reasoning.md §3/§7): the budgeted multi-hop
# inference LOOP. "think deeply: <yes/no question>" parses the target, seeds a
# frontier, and repeatedly ACQUIRES facts from a concept's page (extract_page_facts,
# M2 — each with its source, M1), walks the relation's transitive closure (a C BFS,
# not a recursive solver clause that would explode on a FAILING query), and expands
# the frontier — until the conclusion EMERGES (multi-hop, from SEPARATE sources that
# no single page asserts) or convergence/budget. It reports the conclusion PLUS the
# derivation trace. Deterministic, not generative. Corpus pages are curated static
# snapshots read even in the hermetic suite.

# Study 1 — geographic transitivity: Paris->France (from the Paris page) and
# France->Europe (from the France page); neither page says Paris is in Europe.
> think deeply: is Paris in Europe?
< Yes -- paris is in europe. I derived it across 2 hops: learned capital(paris), located_in(paris, france) (source: paris); learned country(france), located_in(france, western_europe), located_in(france, europe) (source: france); then by transitivity of "located in" it follows that paris is in europe.

# Study 2 — category chain: whale->mammal (whale page) and mammal->vertebrate
# (mammal page), materialized as is_a and closed by transitivity.
> think deeply: is a whale a vertebrate?
< Yes -- a whale is a vertebrate. I derived it across 2 hops: learned mammal(whale), aquatic_animal(whale) (source: whale); learned vertebrate(mammal), animal(mammal) (source: mammal); then by transitivity of "is a" it follows that a whale is a vertebrate.

# Negative control: a conclusion that does NOT follow -> honest decline, never
# invented, with what it did read.
> think deeply: is Paris in Asia?
< I read 2 sources but couldn't derive whether paris is in asia. I learned: learned capital(paris), located_in(paris, france) (source: paris); learned country(france), located_in(france, western_europe), located_in(france, europe) (source: france).

# No question after the trigger -> ask for one, honestly.
> think deeply
< Give me a yes/no question to reason about -- e.g. "think deeply: is Paris in Europe?".

